name: Laís Dib Albuquerque
headline: Software Developer at Sidia | Artificial Intelligence | Deep Learning | Computer Vision | Data Science | Python
experience: Sidia Instituto de Ciência e Tecnologia - Sidia Instituto de Ciência e Tecnologia (User Interface testing is one of the most used routines for Android feature quality verification. Regarding this, several industrial and academic solutions are available for Graphical User Interface component identification. However, the state-of-art works are still limited respecting the variety of widgets that can recognize. Also, most solutions use application metadata that can vary across different releases and device models, affecting the portability of automations. Research that approach widget classification using Machine Learning based solutions commonly use a large Android screen capture dataset called RICO. However, several annotations problems have been recurrently pointed on this dataset. In this work, we propose a selection of data cleaning and balancing techniques for removing noisy samples and leveling the number of samples per class on RICO dataset. We used a custom dataset with an extended number of classes (106) when comparing with the state-of-art works that approach widget classification with 15 classes on average. Finally, we showed that using these techniques to improve the quality of data can improve the accuracy when training Machine Learning models like Convolutional Neural Networks and eXtreme Gradient Boosting.) 2 yrs 1 mo 2 yrs 1 mo Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil · On-site Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil · On-site Full-time Full-time Internship Internship Jun 2023 - Dec 2023 · 7 mos Python, OpenCV and +12 skills Adapting RICO Dataset for Boosting Graphical User Interface Component Classification for Automated Android Testing Adapting RICO Dataset for Boosting Graphical User Interface Component Classification for Automated Android Testing ||| Desenvolvedora de Software - Desenvolvedora de Software (Algoritmos de aprendizado de máquina, Análise de dados and +18 skills) Full-time Full-time ||| Estagiária em Desenvolvimento de Software - Estagiária em Desenvolvimento de Software (User Interface testing is one of the most used routines for Android feature quality verification. Also, most solutions use application metadata that can vary across different releases and device models, affecting the portability of automations. Research that approach widget classification using Machine Learning based solutions commonly use a large Android screen capture dataset called RICO. However, several annotations problems have been recurrently pointed on this dataset. In this work, we propose a selection of data cleaning and balancing techniques for removing noisy samples and leveling the number of samples per class on RICO dataset. We used a custom dataset with an extended number of classes (106) when comparing with the state-of-art works that approach widget classification with 15 classes on average. Finally, we showed that using these techniques to improve the quality of data can improve the accuracy when training Machine Learning models like Convolutional Neural Networks and eXtreme Gradient Boosting.)  ||| Adapting RICO Dataset for Boosting Graphical User Interface Component Classification for Automated Android Testing - Adapting RICO Dataset for Boosting Graphical User Interface Component Classification for Automated Android Testing (User Interface testing is one of the most used routines for Android feature quality verification. It integrates testing into every part of the development process, allowing for early detection and fixing of issues, and enabling faster, high-quality releases.) 6 m Kariny Oliveira The Foundations of Software Testing: Key Concepts for Quality Assurance In the ever-evolving world of software development, quality is non-negotiable. At the heart of ensuring that quality is robust software testing. Understanding the foundations of software testing is essential for anyone involved in development, QA, or any role that requires delivering reliable software products. Here are the core principles every professional should know: 🔍 1. The Importance of Software Testing Testing is vital in verifying that software meets its functional and non-functional requirements, providing confidence that the product will work as expected for users. 🧑‍💻 2. Types of Testing - Manual Testing: Human-driven, exploring the product’s features, detecting bugs and ensuring usability. 🛠️ 4. Key Testing Techniques - Black Box Testing: Focuses on the software's outputs based on inputs, without knowing the internal workings. - Grey Box Testing: A blend of black-box and white-box approaches, testing from the user’s perspective while considering some internal functionality. 📈 6. Metrics for Measuring Success Effective testing goes beyond finding bugs. Metrics like test coverage, defect density, and pass/fail rates help teams measure the effectiveness of their testing and improve processes over time. Why does this matter? Building high-quality software is a team effort, and testing forms the foundation for reliability, security, and user satisfaction. education: Eteocles Silva reposted this - Garima Sangwan (Activate to view larger image,) Garima Sangwan • 3rd+ Verified • 3rd+ 5d • Looks smart. Acts smart. Thinks… exactly like everyone else. I asked 5 AI models for a random number between 1 and 50. ChatGPT? → 27 Claude? → 27 Perplexity? → 27 Gemini? → Yep, 27 Meta ai ? → Still 27 Five different models. One same “random” answer. So… what’s really going on? LLMs aren’t generating randomness. They’re predicting patterns. So what you're seeing isn’t creativity. It’s a mirror. If you're building with GenAI straight out of the box, no fine-tuning, no domain knowledge, no proprietary data - you're not building anything unique. You're just echoing the internet. 💡 Same tools. Same answers. Same blind spots. And that’s exactly what your competitors are doing too. Start by feeding your models something no one else has: Your data. Your edge. Your vision. Otherwise… you're just another 27. hashtag # AI hashtag # ML hashtag # LLMs …more 9,197 870 comments 405 reposts ||| 870 comments - 405 reposts ()  ||| Eteocles Silva - Eteocles Silva (, a pleasure to see this on) • 2nd Verified • 2nd R&D Operations Manager at Samsung Electronics da Amazonia R&D Operations Manager at Samsung Electronics da Amazonia 1w • Edited • "Yours Kids aren't broken. The system is broken" Benjamin Braun Benjamin Braun • 3rd+ Influencer • 3rd+ Chief Marketing Officer at Samsung Europe Chief Marketing Officer at Samsung Europe Chef Jamie Oliver’s brilliant new documentary on dyslexia airs on Monday. It strikes a chord. Like Jamie, I spent a good chunk of my early years being told I was “just not trying hard enough” — when in reality, my brain was just wired differently (still is!). School reports? Let’s just say some weren’t exactly fridge door material. But while spelling tests were traumatic, creative problem-solving, out-of-the-box thinking, and big-picture vision were always effortless for me. Dyslexia isn’t a disadvantage. It’s a different way of seeing the world — one that’s helped me tremendously in my role at Samsung Electronics , where creativity and innovation are the name of the game. Rak Patel Channel 4 . And yes, this little clip was of course filmed and edited on my Samsung Mobile . For the team at The Jamie Oliver Group , amazing work. Respect.
